# Kindle Hardware Test Pass

Use this after installing the KUAL artifact on the Kindle.

## Launch / Exit

- Launch from KUAL.
- Confirm full-screen display.
- Tap **Exit**.
- Relaunch.
- Confirm puzzle state restored.

## New Puzzle Modal

- Tap **New**.
- Confirm size modal appears.
- Select 4x4, 6x6, and 9x9 in separate runs.
- Confirm difficulty modal appears after size selection.
- Select Easy, Normal, Hard, Expert.
- Confirm a new puzzle appears and old state is replaced.

## Board Input

- Select **Normal**.
- Select a number.
- Tap several empty cells.
- Confirm the number remains selected and Normal mode remains active.
- Select **Pencil**.
- Select a number.
- Tap empty cells.
- Confirm the pencil mark appears in the upper-right and the mode remains active.

## Erase

- Select `□`.
- Tap user-entered numbers.
- Tap pencil marks.
- Tap givens.
- Confirm user entries and pencil marks clear, while givens remain unchanged.

## Mistakes

- Enter a known-wrong number.
- Confirm it remains visible with an X through it.
- Confirm it does not cause the number to disappear from the bottom bar.

## Highlighting

- Tap a filled cell.
- Confirm all visible matching numbers invert: black cell, white number.
- Select another number or tap elsewhere.
- Confirm highlight clears.

## Completed Number Auto-Hide

- Complete all instances of a number correctly.
- Confirm that number disappears from the bottom number bar.
- Confirm incorrect X-marked entries and pencil marks do not count.

## Notes to Report Back

When reporting bugs, include:

- Kindle model
- Firmware version
- Puzzle size and difficulty
- Exact tap sequence
- Whether the issue happened after fresh launch or after restore
- A photo of the screen if the issue is visual
